==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Messias|lang=la}}, from Hellenistic {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|Μεσσίας|lang=grc}}, from {{etyl|arc|en}} {{term|משיחא|lang=arc|tr=məšīḥā}}, from {{etyl|hbo|en}} {{term|מָשִׁיחַ||anointed|tr=māšîaḥ|lang=he}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|mə-sī'ə}}, {{IPA|/məˈsaɪ.ə/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|Abrahamic tradition|lang=en}} The one who is ordained by [[God]] to lead the people of [[Israel]], believed by Christians to be [[Jesus Christ]].
# An extremely powerful divine figure.

